Patch Set 3:

You may be wondering why none of the tests failed on the original patch.  Two reasons: (1) they were testing the versions response for the default configuration only, and (2) the v2.10-doesn't-exist test was passing because the float-to-string conversion problem noted inline really was excluding 2.10 from the versions response.  I think the revisions on this patch will break next time if the versions response is changed without the version_negotiation not also being changed, but I'm not 100% sure, so that's something to keep in mind when reviewing.
